🤤🍨

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bissell Brothers in Bissell Brothers with @mentationcannabis. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
Today we release our collab with @mentationcannabis — kindred spirits in dedication to a craft — that celebrates the aromas of our two favorite plants. Mosaic and Simcoe are paired with a blend of terpenes (highly aromatic compounds found in both hops and cannabis) to thread in notes of the hop's famous cousin. Available in cans and pouring on draft when we open at 11am!

**THIS BEER DOES NOT CONTAIN CANNABIS, THC, OR CBD**

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bissell Brothers in Bissell Brothers with @benjamin_martinkovic. node.text:
BBK 🍽 is back for the week with  our Farm BLT on special -🍅 🥬 🥖 🥓 - a simple sandwich made notably delicious by quality produce from @goransonfarm , @farmtotablekids , @solocucinamarket , North Country bacon, and our Fresno vinegar and garlic Mayo! 
Pair it with Granular, our BA gose with sea salt, and beat this mugginess. 

More beers and food specials to come this week- keep the 👀 here!

node.text:
We pled for a re-up from the 
BA mixed-ferm factory @bbbthreerivers and were rewarded! 120 bottles of each of these five beauties are back in stock at HQ for take-away and on-premise consumption - these won’t last long, but don’t worry- four new brands are waiting on labels and will be coming down soon after!

REFILL THIS MONTH, FEATURING: BREWING CoundiloMaine'.

node.text: Join us and @rubbish_portland for a clean up effort on Wednesday July 21st! Meet at the brewery at 5pm, from there we’ll tidy up around Thompson’s Point and beyond (bags and gloves will be provided). Stick around our taproom afterwards for happy hour and a very special raffle featuring some of our favorite local businesses. Head to bissellbrothers.com/events for the link to register!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bissell Brothers on July 13, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: DBL LUX is everything we love about our precious rye pale ale, but properly amplified. Chewy, pillow-soft, and dripping with stone fruit tones. Hopped with tons of hand-selected Mosaic and a kiss of Chinook (as a nod to the original pilot recipe from 2014) with notes of overripe peach, angel food cake, and Orangina. Available now in cans and on draft alongside the original.
